The starting XI for Manchester United’s Premier League tie with Chelsea has been confirmed. Both Man United and Chelsea released their starting XI in a tweet via their Twitter pages on Thursday night. The kick-off time for the game is 7.45 pm, at Old Trafford. Man United’s starting XI: De Gea, Lindelof, Ronaldo, Rashford, Bruno Fernandes, Varane, Dalot, Alex Telles, Matic, Elanga and McTominay Substitutes: Heaton, Henderson, Bailly, Fernadez, Jones, Hannibal, Mata, Garnacho and Shoretire. Chelsea’s starting XI: Mendy, Azpilicueta, Thiago Silva, Rudiger, James, Jorginho, Kante, Alonso, Mount, Havertz and Werner. Substitutes: Kepa, Chalobah, Sarr, Loftus-Cheek, Saul Kenedy, Pulisic, Ziyech and Lukaku